    <h2>&#128214; About Me</h2>
    <img src="/assets/country-road.png" alt="Country Road Image">
    <p>
      I was born and raised in the Southern Downs, QLD. I had 
      interests in sport, art, and music in my youth, but it 
      wasn't until I finished highschool and spent some time
      in Brisbane that I discovered programming.
    </p>
    <p>
      I distinctly remember wishing that I had more time to understand
      maths when I was finishing year 12. So, when I left, I decided
      to spend some time doing independent study.
    </p>
    <p>
      Hospitality can be a good flexible choice for work when you
      want time for other things, so I worked in a restaurant and
      learned about logic and set theory in my spare time. I delved
      right in to the nitty-gritty of it all, and somewhere along
      the line I came across programming. 
    </p>
    <p>
      I loved the formal aspects of maths and logic, and programming
      involved the same kind of thinking, but it was also a whole lot
      more - a highly practical and very creative application of what 
      I had been investigating! 
    </p>
  </section>
