    </p>
    <h3>IDE</h3>
    <p>
      The most recent project that I've been working on is an IDE built with TypeScript
      and Electron.js. It's been the most challenging software that I've attempted
      so far - an incredibly rewarding process. I actually initially began the project
      with C++ using the Qt GUI toolkit, but later decided that I wanted to use Electron.
      The first version with Electron involved the use of vanilla JS and custom HTML elements, 
      and I got as far as implementing syntax highlighting. However, I decided to make the
      application a little more robust and rewrote what I'd done so far in TypeScript.
      I haven't reached a stage where I'm ready to publish this project yet, but I'd be 
      happy to add the curious as collaborators!
    </p>
    <p>
